==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Omphalode
<hw>Om"pha*lode</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Omphalo-</ets> + Gr. <grk>e'i^dos</grk> form.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The central part of the hilum of a seed, through
which the nutrient vessels pass into the rhaphe or the chalaza; --
called also <altname>omphalodium</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Omphalomancy</ent>⟦br⟧
